"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446215","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-26","<br /><p>The Government has previously stated that it is seeking to sell a majority stake in the Green Investment Bank (GIB) in the financial year 2016/17.</p><br /><p>Strong market interest currently exists for the GIB and we expect this timetable to be successfully met. Any extension would be considered nearer to the end of that timetable, should it be required.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-26T14:24:38.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446215/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446215/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Green Investment Bank: Privatisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the timescale is for privatisation of the Green Investment Bank; and whether he has made contingency plans to extend that timescale in the event of adverse market conditions.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","23450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446216","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Skills Funding Agency (SFA) is working closely with the Department for Work and Pensions (DWP). A live link from the ‘Find an Apprenticeship’ service provides real time apprenticeship vacancies each day to the Jobcentre Plus Universal Jobmatch vacancy website. This ensures that clients who are in receipt of benefits have easy access to information about apprenticeship vacancies.</p><br /><p>In addition, the SFA is working with DWP to train work coaches in job centres so that they have up to date information on apprenticeships to share with clients. The SFA is also ensuring that DWP employer teams have the information needed on apprenticeships to promote these as part of their conversations with businesses.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-27T14:51:00.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446216/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446216/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Jobcentre Plus: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what discussions officials in his Department have had with officials of the Department for Work and Pensions on JobCentre Plus involvement in the Find An Apprentice Service.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","23454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446217","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-29","<p>The table below outlines the total number of staff employed by full-time equivalence in the Skills Funding Agency:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>1459</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>1580</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>1200</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>1142</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>788</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Staffing numbers have reduced as part of the Civil Service reform programme. Alongside this, the Skills Funding Agency has prioritised its resources to focus on 3 million apprenticeship starts. The latest Statistical First Release shows an upward trajectory of apprenticeship starts.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-02-29T09:39:47.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446217/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446217/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446217/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Skills Funding Agency: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many full-time equivalent staff there were in the Skills Funding Agency in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13, (d) 2013-14 and (e) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","23452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446218","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-28","<br /><p>The National Apprenticeship Service is part of the Skills Funding Agency. We plan for this to continue to be the case in 2016-17.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-28T17:16:22.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446218/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446218/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446218/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Skills Funding Agency: Apprentices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether the National Apprenticeship Service will continue to be (a) administered and (b) funded through the Skills Funding Agency in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","23453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446219","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-27","<p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>The consultation was published on 25 January 2016.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-27T15:20:03.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446219/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446219/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446219/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Apprentices: Public Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he plans to launch his Department's consultation for target numbers of apprenticeships in the public sector.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","23507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446220","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-28","<p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>Data on the value of freight that was imported by sea into the UK in each of the last five years is available from Eurostat’s Comext database (“EXTRA-EU Trade since 1999 by mode of transport”). This data covers only UK imports by sea from the Non-EU countries. Data by mode of transport for intra-EU trade is not available in value terms.</p><br /><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-28T17:20:30.177Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446220/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446220/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Freight: Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what value of freight was imported by sea into the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446221","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Institute for Apprenticeships, a new independent body led by employers, is being established to oversee the quality of apprenticeships in England.</p><br /><p>The Institute for Apprenticeships will put in place transparent mechanisms for the approval of apprenticeship standards and assessment plans, and maintain clear quality criteria so that only standards that are valued by employers will be approved and funded.</p><br /><p>It will be fully operational by April 2017.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-01-27T15:21:57.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446221/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446221/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446221/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Apprentices: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what additional checks on standards and quality his Department and the National Apprenticeship Service plan to introduce in response to the targets listed in his Department's publication, English Apprenticeships: Our 2020 Vision, published on 7 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","23508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446222","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-28","<p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>Increasing exports is a key factor in the Government’s long-term economic plan. Government departments are working together to support UK businesses looking to take advantage of overseas opportunities and to create a strong business environment that allows UK businesses to flourish both at home and overseas.</p><br /><p>My noble Friend Lord Maude of Horsham made a <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-statement/Lords/2016-01-19/HLWS466/" target="_blank">statement</a> to the House on Tuesday 19<sup>th</sup> January on the Government’s strategy to support Trade. This outlines a new, whole-of-government approach to expanding the number of exporters and the value they generate for the British economy. The aim is to make it easier for small business to access this support through better digital platforms, working more closely with partners and making sure services match the needs of business.</p><br /><p>In addition, the cross-Government ‘One Government at the Border’ (OG@B) will focus on simplifying the experience of moving goods in and out of the UK, especially for those businesses which are smaller and new to exporting.</p><br /><p>The UK is currently ranked by the World Economic Forum and the World Bank within the top 10 countries in the world for ease of doing business. The British Business Bank offers £2.4bn of finance to over 40,000 smaller businesses. Included within this is the Start-Up Loans programme, which has provided over 35,000 loans worth over £192 million. We have saved businesses £10 billion of red tape and we have extended small business rate relief.</p><br /><p>The Government will continue to back small firms to grow at home and overseas and to create jobs by providing an environment in which they can thrive. This means cutting a further £10 billion of red tape, extending business rates relief, tackling late payment culture and improving access to finance. Through these and other support mechanisms the Government is committed to helping an additional 100,000 companies export successfully by 2020 compared to 2010.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-28T17:22:09.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446222/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446222/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446222/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Small Businesses: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to reduce export costs for businesses to encourage small and medium-sized enterprises to increase their levels of exports.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446223","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-28","<br /><p>The Government works closely with the automotive industry, in particular through the Automotive Council, on competitiveness issues affecting the sector. In November 2015, the Automotive Council published an assessment of the UK’s international competitiveness on their website. UK automotive sector productivity is the highest in Europe compared to other major European producers. Car production reached a 10-year high in 2015 at 1.59 million vehicles, with almost 80% of these exported to over 100 countries. In addition, the value of UK sourced components by vehicle manufacturers has increased from 36% in 2011 to 41% in 2015. The sector is at the forefront in the design and use of high quality Apprenticeships to ensure the skilled workforce required to support future growth.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-28T17:38:11.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446223/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446223/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446223/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Motor Vehicles: Trade Competitiveness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his Department has made an assessment of the impact of its policies on the automotive sector on the competitiveness of that sector.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446224","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-28","<p><strong></strong></p><p><strong></strong></p><br /><p>The Government recognises that late payment remains an important issue for small businesses in the UK and is taking significant steps to assist small businesses to recover late payment debts. This is part of a package of measures to tackle late payment. We have also legislated for new transparency measures in the private sector.</p><br /><p>The Small Business Enterprise and Employment Act 2015 legislated for a new reporting requirement on the UK’s largest companies and Regulations will be introduced this year which will compel larger companies to report on payment practices and performance. This information will be published on a six-monthly basis and will be made publicly available.</p><br /><p>Through the Enterprise Bill, currently before Parliament, we will legislate to establish a Small Business Commissioner to give general advice and to help small businesses resolve disputes relating to payment matters with larger businesses.</p><br /><p>Tackling late payment is about creating a responsible payment culture where larger companies recognise the benefit of having a sustainable and robust supply chain, and smaller businesses feel able to challenge poor behaviour. Once implemented, the Government is confident that these measures will lead to significant changes in the UK’s payment culture.</p><br /><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-01-28T17:36:16.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446224/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446224/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446224/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-20","Small Businesses: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps his Department is taking to encourage larger companies to make payments to small and medium-sized enterprises on time.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23500"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446225","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-28","<p>Over 200,000 young people have benefitted from the National Citizen Service (NCS) since 2011. In 2014 57,789 young people took part. The figure for 2015 will be made available after an independent evaluation later this year.</p><p>The Prime Minister has announced the ambition to expand the programme to 60% of all 16 year olds by 2021 and this is the target we aim to deliver.</p><p>The funding for NCS was announced in the autumn statement and spending review. More than £1billion has been committed to the expansion of NCS in this parliament.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","23302 ; 23331","2016-01-28T16:28:53.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446225/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446225/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446225/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-20","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many young people participated in the National Citizen Service in 2015.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","23330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446226","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-28","<p>Over 200,000 young people have benefitted from the National Citizen Service (NCS) since 2011. In 2014 57,789 young people took part. The figure for 2015 will be made available after an independent evaluation later this year.</p><p>The Prime Minister has announced the ambition to expand the programme to 60% of all 16 year olds by 2021 and this is the target we aim to deliver.</p><p>The funding for NCS was announced in the autumn statement and spending review. More than £1billion has been committed to the expansion of NCS in this parliament.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","23302 ; 23330","2016-01-28T16:28:53.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446226/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446226/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446226/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-20","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what forecast he has made of the number of young people that will participate in the National Citizen Service in each year from 2015 to 2020.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","23331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446227","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-25","<p>The Government Property Unit have developed guidelines and a standardised commercial agreement for Departments to make it easier for mobile telephone operatorsto erect masts on Government buildings. Government Property Unit also provided a London Rate Card for use by Departments and Mobile Network Operators (MNOs) that sets out indicative rents for a range of locations. The Government Property Unit have also issued further technical guidance for Departments' Estates.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-01-25T17:08:15.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446227/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446227/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446227/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-20","Aerials","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether his Department has (a) guidelines and (b) a template contract for the leasing of government property to mobile telephone operators for the purposes of erecting masts.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","23300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446228","Cabinet Office","false","2016-01-28","<p>Over 200,000 young people have benefitted from the National Citizen Service (NCS) since 2011. In 2014 57,789 young people took part. The figure for 2015 will be made available after an independent evaluation later this year.</p><p>The Prime Minister has announced the ambition to expand the programme to 60% of all 16 year olds by 2021 and this is the target we aim to deliver.</p><p>The funding for NCS was announced in the autumn statement and spending review. More than £1billion has been committed to the expansion of NCS in this parliament.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","23330 ; 23331","2016-01-28T16:28:53.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446228/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446228/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446228/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-01-20","Voluntary Work: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will estimate the annual cost of providing places on the National Citizen Service for all children aged 16 and 17.","false","Biography information for Liam Byrne","Birmingham, Hodge Hill","Liam Byrne","23302"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446229","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-25","<p>The Government has not received any representations on the number of complaints to the Financial Ombudsman Service (FOS) in relation to the mis-selling of packaged bank accounts.</p><br /><p>The FOS publishes an annual review of the complaints handled by the service. Its most recent report, including details of the complaints it has received about packaged bank accounts, can be accessed online at <a href="http://www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/publications/ar15/ar15pdf" target="_blank">www.financial-ombudsman.org.uk/publications/ar15/ar15pdf</a>. In addition, Treasury ministers meet with the Chief Ombudsman to discuss the Financial Ombudsman Service’s work.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-25T15:05:39.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446229/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446229/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446229/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-20","Bank Services: Misrepresentation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations he has had on the number of complaints to the Financial Ombudsman in relation to the misselling of packaged bank accounts; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","23255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446230","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-28","<p>There are no plans to review the payments made by the Equitable Life Payment Scheme. The Scheme closed to new claims on 31<sup>st</sup> December 2015. However, the annual payments to With-Profits Annuitants will continue unaffected for the duration of their annuity.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-28T14:33:59.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446230/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446230/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446230/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-20","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans the Government has to review the amount of compensation for losses paid to Equitable Life policy holders over the course of the current Parliament.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","23265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446231","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-25","<p>Britain is in a much stronger economic position than five years ago, with employment at 74% and the deficit down. However, as the Chancellor set out in his speech on 7 January, we face a dangerous cocktail of economic risks from around the world this year. The International Monetary Fund has revised down their forecasts for world growth in 2016 and 2017, while the UK forecasts remain unchanged. This shows that the best thing that we can do is to continue to fix our public finances, back business and deliver our long-term economic plan.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-25T15:54:53.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446231/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446231/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446231/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-20","Economic Situation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what he assesses to be the major risks to the UK economy.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","23378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446232","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-27","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) policy in respect of compensation payments is that they will consider refunding any reasonable costs that customers may have incurred due to their mistakes and/or unreasonable delays. If HMRC actions are judged to have affected a customer particularly badly, they may pay a small amount to acknowledge their mistake and for any worry or distress they may have caused. These payments are made out of the public purse and are not intended to put a monetary value on any worry and upset.</p><br />","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-27T14:49:27.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446232/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446232/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446232/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-20","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2016 to Question 22263, what procedures, budgets and facilities are in place to compensate tax credit claimants for the cost and inconvenience of losing supporting documents confirming identity and finances lost by the Tax Credit Office.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","23398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446233","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-25","<p>Further information on the impact of the changes to the LCF announced at Autumn Statement 2015 is set out in <em>Reform and value of the Landfill Communities Fund. </em>This document can be found here:</p><p><br> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/reform-and-value-of-the-landfill-communities-fund/reform-and-value-of-the-landfill-communities-fund" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/reform-and-value-of-the-landfill-communities-fund/reform-and-value-of-the-landfill-communities-fund</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2016-01-25T10:30:11.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446233/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446233/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446233/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-20","Landfill Communities Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the proposed removal of third party contributions from the Landfill Communities Fund on (a) the future availability of funding for community and biodiversity projects and (b) environmental bodies.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","23479"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446234","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-28","<p>There are no plans to review the payments made by the Equitable Life Payment Scheme. The Scheme closed to new claims on 31<sup>st</sup> December 2015. However, the annual payments to With-Profits annuitants will continue unaffected for the duration of their annuity.</p><br />","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-01-28T14:32:11.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446234/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446234/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446234/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-20","Equitable Life Assurance Society: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Government plans to increase the compensation available to Equitable Life pensioners.","false","Biography information for John Pugh","Southport","John Pugh","23468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446235","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-28","<p>Local authorities are responsible for the administration and delivery of the Communities and Business Recovery Scheme.</p><p>They determine how to use the money to best meet local need and ensure value for money. My Department does not collect detailed information on the payments that have been made through the Scheme. However, officials are aware that of more that 15,000 payments made to households, fewer than 50 have been found to be incorrect. Those have been returned to the local authority in question.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-01-28T16:46:40.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446235/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446235/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446235/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Floods: Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 19 January 2016 to Question 22026, what proportion of the £47 million paid to local authorities under the Communities and Business Recovery Scheme was subsequently paid by local authorities to households which were not entitled to flood compensation payments.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","23341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446236","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-25","<p>It is up to individual local authorities to set their policies for sandbag distribution and allocation to residents based on flood risk.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-01-25T15:45:41.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446236/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446236/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446236/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Housing: Flood Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy to ensure that borough councils in two-tier authority areas provide sandbags to all residents to protect their properties during incidents of flooding.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","23402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446237","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-27","<p>There is no record of any occasion during 2014 or 2015 where the Department has been notified centrally by outside consultants or other third parties of breaches by employees or subcontractors of those consultants of document retention or security policies relating to confidential or secure materials.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-01-27T17:08:48.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446237/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446237/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446237/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Department for Communities and Local Government: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, on how many occasions in each of the last two calendar years his Department has been notified by outside consultants or other third parties of breaches by employees or subcontractors of those consultants of document retention or security policies relating to confidential or secure materials.","false","Biography information for Stephen Phillips","Sleaford and North Hykeham","Stephen Phillips","23349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446238","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-26","<p>Local authorities, familiar with stock in their areas, are best placed to set up appropriate inspection plans that take account of resources available and risk posed by individual properties. The Government has no plans to require six-monthly inspections of licensed houses in multiple occupation and bed and breakfast accommodation occupied by homeless persons.</p><p>Local housing authorities must also exercise their functions in respect of hazards under the Housing, Health and Safety Rating System in relation to licensed houses in multiple occupation and ensure any accommodation they secure to accommodate homeless households is suitable. In considering &quot;suitability&quot; authorities must consider whether the accommodation is affordable for the household, its size, its condition, its accessibility and also its location.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-01-26T14:57:51.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446238/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446238/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446238/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Multiple Occupation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy to require six-monthly inspections of all licensed houses in multiple occupation and bed and breakfasts catering for homeless people.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","23439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446239","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-01-28","<p>The Department continues to liaise with a range of key stakeholders as it develops exemptions to the removal of automatic entitlement to housing support for 18-21 year olds in Universal Credit. This includes discussing this policy with landlords, housing associations and charities.</p><p>Once this work has been completed we will bring forward detailed proposals.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-01-28T13:26:16.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446239/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446239/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446239/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-01-20","Universal Credit: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 23 November 2015 to Question 16318, what recent progress he has made on discussions with stakeholders on proposals to exempt certain groups from the removal of automatic entitlement to housing support for 18 to 21 years olds on universal credit; and when he plans to publish proposals resulting from those discussions.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","23440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446240","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-28","<p>Information on homeless households not in priority need is already collected and published in table 770 of the homelessness live tables which can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness</a></p><p>No information is collected on the household type of households found to be not in priority need.</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","23445","2016-01-28T16:44:49.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446240/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446240/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446240/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will bring forward plans to (a) require all local authorities to measure the level of single non-priority homelessness in their areas and (b) collate that data in a national database.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","23444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446241","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-28","<p>Information on homeless households not in priority need is already collected and published in table 770 of the homelessness live tables which can be viewed at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-homelessness</a></p><p>No information is collected on the household type of households found to be not in priority need.</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","23444","2016-01-28T16:44:49.32Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446241/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446241/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446241/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of non-priority single homeless people in the UK in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","23445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446242","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-27","<p>Under the Ministry of Justice’s Transformation Rehabilitation reforms, Community Rehabilitation Companies are contractually required to deliver a range of ‘Through the Gate’ resettlement services to offenders. This involves working with offenders before release to assess their housing needs, including helping them to secureaccommodation and maintain tenancies post release.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-01-27T17:07:31.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446242/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446242/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446242/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Housing: Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what housing support is provided to ex-offenders on leaving prison; and if he will bring forward legislative proposals to introduce a statutory requirement to provide settled accommodation for ex-offenders.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","23462"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446243","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-27","<p>Under Part 7 of the Housing Act 1996, households that include someone who is vulnerable, for example because of old age, physical or mental disability or any other special reason, have a priority need for accommodation. Housing authorities must ensure that suitable accommodation is available for anyone if they are in priority need, are eligible for assistance and unintentionally homeless.</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-01-27T17:09:36.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446243/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446243/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446243/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Social Rented Housing: Vulnerable Adults","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to ensure that vulnerable people are prioritised in the provision of settled accommodation.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","23326"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446244","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-01-28","<p>Information and data on a prisoner’s housing destination at the point of discharge from prison is published at:</p><br /><p>2014-15:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/451037/mi-addendum.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/451037/mi-addendum.xls</a></p><p>2013-14:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/338947/mi-addendum-dataset-2013-14.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/338947/mi-addendum-dataset-2013-14.xls</a></p><p>2012/13</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225233/mi-addendum-dataset.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/225233/mi-addendum-dataset.xls</a></p><p>2011/12:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/218334/noms-annual-report-addendum-2011-12.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/218334/noms-annual-report-addendum-2011-12.xls</a></p><br /><p>2010/11:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/218346/noms-annual-report-2010-11-addendum.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/218346/noms-annual-report-2010-11-addendum.pdf</a></p><br /><p>For the purposes of the performance measure, settled accommodation covers the following categories: permanent housing, supported housing, approved premises, other hostels and Bail Accommodation &amp; Support Service (BASS) accommodation.</p><p>Not in settled accommodation means: transient/short term accommodation, no fixed address, or no Information.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2016-01-28T17:54:55.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446244/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446244/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446244/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-01-20","Housing: Offenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the (a) number and (b) proportion of ex-offenders leaving prison who were provided (i) settled and (ii) temporary accommodation in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","23419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446245","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-27","<p>Guidance on the tree preservation legislation is published on the planning guidance website at <a href="http://planningguidance.communities.gov.uk/blog/guidance/tree-preservation-orders/" target="_blank">http://planningguidance.communities.gov.uk/blog/guidance/tree-preservation-orders/</a> and is available to local authorities and other interested parties. Local authorities are responsible for determining applications for works to trees protected by Tree Preservation Orders.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2016-01-27T17:03:18.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446245/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446245/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Trees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department issues to local authorities on ensuring that consent is granted before a person undertakes work on a neighbour's tree.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","23247"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446246","Department for Education","false","2016-01-26","<p>We want to ensure that as many children as possible who are eligible for free school meals (FSM) receive them. We have made it as simple as possible for schools and local authorities to check eligibility. We are aware that a number of local authorities have been successful in using housing benefit and council tax support claim data to identify children who may be eligible for, but are not currently claiming, FSM.</p><p>We are looking in more detail at the approaches that schools and local authorities have taken so far and we will set out the Government’s position on this issue shortly.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2016-01-26T13:55:13.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446246/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446246/answer","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446246/answer/previousversion/40963","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","60","Education","Education","2016-01-20","Free School Meals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will assess the potential merits of enabling or compelling local authorities to use housing and council tax benefit data to (a) identify children who are eligible for free school meals and the pupil premium and (b) enable parents and guardians of those children to claim free school meals for their children.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","23261"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446247","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-01-25","<p>A reply was sent on 21 January.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-01-25T15:46:32.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446247/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446247/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-01-20","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will arrange for the hon. Member for Walsall North to receive a reply to his letter of 9 December 2015 on behalf of a social housing provider in his constituency.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","23258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446248","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-03","<p>DCMS funds the promotion of tourism to regions of the UK through the activities of its Arms Length Body, the British Tourist Authority, which trades as both VisitEngland and VisitBritain. In the recent Spending Review, it was announced that grant-in-aid to both VisitEngland and VisitBritain would remain stable to 2020. The Chancellor also announced a new £40m Discover England fund, which will be open to all regions of England. In addition, the GREAT campaign funds the promotion of Britain: its nations and regions, in overseas markets.</p><p> </p><p>Over the past three years, there have been a number of funding streams for specific regions, including the Northern and South West Tourism Growth Funds in 2015/16 and the Regional Growth Fund 'Growing Tourism Locally' programme, which ran for three years from 2012-15. As many projects and campaigns span the whole of England or the UK, investment figures cannot be divided by region.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-02-03T16:17:23.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446248/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446248/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446248/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-20","Tourism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what funding streams his Department has for the promotion of tourism to UK regions; and what proportion of those funds was spent on each region in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","23251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446249","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Government wants to reduce the cost and hassle of switching mobile providers for consumers. We expect industry to start automatically unlocking customers’ handsets at the end of their contracts, and will consult this year on ending the practice of handset locking for customers outside their initial contract period.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-01-27T13:43:15.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446249/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446249/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446249/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-20","Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will discuss with mobile telephone companies steps to reduce and standardise the time between a provider unlocking a phone and the owner of that phone being able to use it with another provider.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","23249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446250","HM Treasury","false","2016-01-28","<p>Creative sector tax reliefs play an important role in stimulating investment in an industry that employs 1.8 million people and provides world-class cultural experiences to many more.</p><br /><p>HM Revenue and Customs published official statistics in December 2015 showing that a record 220 films claimed the film tax credit in 2014-15, with the relief supporting over £1bn worth of UK expenditure in the sector.</p><br /><p>Since the reliefs came into force in 2013-14, the high-end TV tax relief has supported almost £600m of expenditure in the industry and the animation tax relief has supported £68 million. Official statistics for the creative sector tax reliefs can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/creative-industries-statistics-december-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/creative-industries-statistics-december-2015</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-01-28T11:40:56.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446250/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446250/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446250/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-20","Arts: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of the Government's tax reliefs on (a) the film and (b) other creative industries.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","23413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446251","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-01","<p>DCMS is working with other Government Departments and our delivery partners to ensure that people of all ages can take part in commemorations of the First World War and remember those who sacrificed so much. As part of the FWW centenary commemorations, the government is providing the opportunity for two pupils and one teacher from every state-funded secondary school in England to visit the FWW battlefields on the Western Front. In 2015, 1,140 Schools and 3,489 pupils and teachers visited FWW battlefields on the Western Front. Since July 2014, 54,702 children and young people visited the Imperial War Museums First World War Galleries as part of a school visit. Over 21,400 people from the UK and overseas wrote a letter for the 'Letter to an Unknown Soldier' project, engaging over 500 primary and secondary schools across the UK. On 4 August 2014, 1.4 million 16-24 year olds participated in LIGHTS OUT – an initiative to light a candle in remembrance. As well as the official commemoration programme schools across the UK are organising their own individual events and projects to remember those who took part in the First World War in battle and on the home front.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-02-01T14:50:50.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446251/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446251/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446251/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-20","World War I: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps his Department has taken to ensure the maximum level of engagement by children and young people with the commemoration of the First World War.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","23393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446252","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-09","<p>My officials have regular discussions with betting operators on a wide range of issues.</p><p>The Government keeps under review ways to support investment in good causes, including the recommendations of the Use of Dormant Betting Accounts Report.</p><p>Ministers continue to encourage the gambling industry to maximise their contributions to these important areas, including funding programmes of research, prevention, and treatment of gambling-related harm,</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","23344","2016-02-09T13:34:12.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446252/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446252/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-20","Betting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 16 March 2015 to Question 227069, whether his Department has yet considered the recommendations of the Use of Dormant Betting Accounts Report, relating to the use of money from dormant betting accounts and unclaimed winnings held by betting operators for investment in good causes.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","23340"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446253","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-09","<p>My officials have regular discussions with betting operators on a wide range of issues.</p><p>The Government keeps under review ways to support investment in good causes, including the recommendations of the Use of Dormant Betting Accounts Report.</p><p>Ministers continue to encourage the gambling industry to maximise their contributions to these important areas, including funding programmes of research, prevention, and treatment of gambling-related harm,</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett","23340","2016-02-09T13:34:12.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446253/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446253/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-01-20","Betting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions his Department has had with betting operators to ascertain how much is held in dormant betting accounts and unclaimed winnings.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","23344"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446254","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Prime Minister discussed the scope of the Intelligence and Security Committee's (ISC) Inquiry with its Chairman. They reached agreement on the disclosure of material to the ISC that will enable the Committee to conduct a review of the threat posed by Reyaad Khan. The ISC have received contemporaneous intelligence assessments of Khan and will take further evidence in the coming weeks.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-01-27T16:08:20.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446254/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446254/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether any person or body has sought disclosure of documents relevant to the decision to target Reyaad Khan by drone strike in Syria on 21 August 2015 for purposes related to the Inquiry by the Intelligence and Security Committee into that matter.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","23432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446255","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>The UK and the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia have a long history of defence cooperation. As part of this long standing relationship, the RAF provides training and shares best practice to the Royal Saudi Air Force, including training on International Humanitarian Law (IHL) compliant targeting.</p><p>In addition we have provided guidance and advice to the Saudis on their processes to ensure continued compliance with IHL.</p><p>Finally the UK has deployed a small number of military personnel serving as Liaison Officers in Saudi headquarters. Their role is to build our relationship and provide insight into Saudi operations. Liaison Officers are not involved in directing or conducting operations in Yemen or selecting targets and are not involved in the Saudi targeting decision-making process.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-01-25T16:24:51.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446255/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446255/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Yemen: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assistance British service personnel are providing to Saudi Arabian forces in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","23505"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446256","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-27","<p>Clause 21 of the Armed Forces Bill provides for the Bill’s extent outside the United Kingdom. Clause 21(1) deals specifically with extent in the Channel Islands. By extent, we mean the jurisdictions outside the United Kingdom in which the Bill’s provisions will, or may, form part of the law. There are no provisions in the Bill which extend automatically to the Channel Islands but the changes that the Bill makes to the Armed Forces Act 2006 may be extended there by Order in Council (though it does not necessarily follow that such an Order will be made). The other changes that the Bill makes (such as changes to the powers of MOD fire-fighters) may not be extended to the Channel Islands.</p><br /><p>We are not currently aware of any requirements which would necessitate an Order in Council being made to extend to the Channel Islands any of the changes that the Bill makes to the Armed Forces Act 2006. However, it should be noted that the question of whether the 2006 Act extends to (i.e. forms part of the law of) the Channel Islands is entirely separate from the question of whether members of the Armed Forces are subject to the 2006 Act as a matter of UK law when they are in the Channel Islands. As a matter of UK law, the 2006 Act applies to members of the Armed Forces wherever they are in the world.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-01-27T16:06:00.283Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446256/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446256/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Armed Forces Bill: Channel Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the timescale is for the extension of the provisions of the Armed Forces Bill to the Channel Islands.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","23501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446257","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>The transport of Defence Nuclear Material is regulated by the Defence Nuclear Safety Regulator according to the provisions of Joint Service Publication 538, Regulation of the Nuclear Weapon Programme, available at: www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/341332/20140801_JSP_538_V3_1_Pt_1.pdf</p><p>A wide range of safety and contingency measures are in place to ensure the safety of nuclear convoy operations. These are summarised in the Local Authority and Emergency Service Information document available at: www.gov.uk/government/publications/local-authority-emergency-services-information.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","23384","2016-01-25T16:16:20.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446257/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446257/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Radioactive Materials: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how the movement of nuclear materials on roads in Scotland by his Department is supervised and regulated.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","23386"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446258","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>It is Ministry of Defence policy not to comment upon the frequency or routes used by nuclear material convoys, as to do so would, or would be likely to, prejudice national security. Nuclear material convoy movements are kept to the minimum necessary to maintain the operational effectiveness of the UK's nuclear deterrent.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","23385","2016-01-25T16:17:44.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446258/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446258/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Radioactive Materials: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many movements of nuclear material there have been on roads in Scotland in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","23374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446259","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Strategic Defence and Security Review (SDSR) provides the investment necessary to deliver the most modern Navy in the world, capable of delivering effect around the globe. The SDSR sets out plans to grow the capability and manpower of the Royal Navy, including a renewed Strategic Deterrent; 100% Aircraft Carrier availability from two carriers; more F-35B jets, with 24 embarked on the Aircraft Carriers from 2023 or earlier; at least 19 Frigates and Destroyers including Type 45 Destroyers, Type 26 Frigates and a new generation of credible general purpose frigates; new Offshore Patrol Vessels and new tanker support ships; and nine New Maritime Patrol Aircraft, working alongside our submarines and frigates to protect the Deterrent and our Aircraft Carriers and keep our seas safe.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-01-27T16:12:34.88Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446259/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446259/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446259/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Navy: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the implications of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 for the Royal Navy's global reach.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","23411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446260","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>The Scottish Government and local authorities are not given advance notice of movements that involve Defence nuclear material.</p><p>Police forces are always notified in advance of a convoy being routed through their area. Police may advise fire and rescue services of the presence of the convoy if it is moving into the vicinity of a fire service operation.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-01-25T16:17:00.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446260/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446260/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446260/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Radioactive Materials: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what advisory notices of movements of nuclear material by road in Scotland his Department gives to (a) the Scottish Government and (b) Scottish local authorities in advance of any such movements.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","23383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446261","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>The transport of Defence Nuclear Material is regulated by the Defence Nuclear Safety Regulator according to the provisions of Joint Service Publication 538, Regulation of the Nuclear Weapon Programme, available at: www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/341332/20140801_JSP_538_V3_1_Pt_1.pdf</p><p>A wide range of safety and contingency measures are in place to ensure the safety of nuclear convoy operations. These are summarised in the Local Authority and Emergency Service Information document available at: www.gov.uk/government/publications/local-authority-emergency-services-information.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","23386","2016-01-25T16:16:20.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446261/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446261/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446261/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Radioactive Materials: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what safety and contingency measures his Department puts in place before nuclear materials are transported on roads in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","23384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446262","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>It is Ministry of Defence policy not to comment upon the frequency or routes used by nuclear material convoys, as to do so would, or would be likely to, prejudice national security. Nuclear material convoy movements are kept to the minimum necessary to maintain the operational effectiveness of the UK's nuclear deterrent.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","23374","2016-01-25T16:17:44.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446262/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446262/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446262/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Radioactive Materials: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what road routes have been used for the movement of nuclear materials in Scotland in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","23385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446263","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>I met Pakistan's Defence Minister, Khawaja Muhammad Asif, on 5 August 2015.</p><p>During my visit I also paid calls on the Prime Minister and other key interlocutors. Most recently, I met with Pakistan's Chief of Army Staff, General Raheel Sharif when he visited the UK last October.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-01-25T16:24:07.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446263/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446263/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446263/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Pakistan: Foreign Relations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when he last met his Pakistani counterpart.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","23338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446264","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-27","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) holds records of former employees of the MOD who have applied to serve in foreign militaries under the Business Appointments process. However, it is not known if these individuals went on to take up the appointment.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-01-27T16:07:52.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446264/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446264/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446264/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Ministry of Defence: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department keeps a record of former employees of the Ministry of Defence who are now serving in foreign militaries.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","23339"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446265","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-26","<br /><p>None.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier","23129","2016-01-26T15:43:25.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446265/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446265/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446265/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","France: Military Alliances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what analysis his Department has commissioned of the potential effect of a British withdrawal from the EU on Anglo-French defence projects.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","23361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446266","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-25","<p>An armed conflict was occuring in Syria at the time of the air strike on 21 August 2015.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-01-25T16:18:29.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446266/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446266/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446266/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference his oral evidence to the Joint Committee on Human Rights of 16 December 2015, Question 20, HC 574, whether his Department's position was that the UK was in an armed conflict (a) before, (b) on the date of or (c) as a result of the drone strike that killed Reyaad Khan of 21 August 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","23435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446267","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-27","<p>In the calendar year 2014 the Ministry of Defence (MOD) was notified of 142 breaches involving document retention or security policies relating to confidential or secure materials by external consultants or other third parties respectively.</p><p>In the calendar year 2015 the MOD was notified of 144 breaches involving document retention or security policies relating to confidential or secure materials by external consultants or other third parties.</p><p>The MOD treats the security of its information very seriously and requires all breaches - however minor - to be reported. All such incidents are subjected to an initial security risk assessment, with further action taken on a proportionate basis.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-01-27T16:07:19.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446267/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446267/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446267/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Ministry of Defence: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, on how many occasions his Department has been notified by external consultants or other third parties of breaches by employees or subcontractors of those consultants of document retention or security policies relating to confidential or secure materials.","false","Biography information for Stephen Phillips","Sleaford and North Hykeham","Stephen Phillips","23346"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446268","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-27","<p>As part of the Surface Ship Support Alliance between the Ministry of Defence, BAE Systems and Babcock Marine, the relative distribution of engineering workload is subject to regular assessment. This ensures that peaks and troughs of workload are managed to ensure key skills are maintained across the Naval Bases, engineering outputs are delivered in accordance with the needs of the Royal Navy, and the Department obtains best value for money from its industry partners.</p><p>The workload allocation for submarines is dictated by a clearly defined programme of work designed to meet the operational requirements of the Fleet. This programme has been constructed noting the capability and capacity of Her Majesty's Naval Bases at Clyde and Devonport and work is allocated accordingly.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-01-27T16:09:28.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446268/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446268/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Navy: Military Bases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the relative distribution of engineering workload across naval bases; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","23270"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446269","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-01-27","<p>No.</p><br />","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2016-01-27T16:02:35.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446269/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/446269/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-01-20","Unmanned Air Vehicles: Deployment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will make it his policy that the House be given an opportunity to debate in advance any decision to deploy UK Reaper aircraft outside Syria and Iraq.","false","Biography information for Mr David Anderson","Blaydon","Mr David Anderson","23290"
